his function uses a different algorithm (called DFA, i.e. deterministic","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"finite automaton), so it can retrieve all the possible matches, all","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"starting at the same point in the string. For instance matching"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"<a> <b> <c>\""},{"type":"text","text":" against the pattern "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"<.*>\""},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you would obtain three matches: "},{"code":"\"<a> <b> <c>\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"\"<a> <b>\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"<a>\""},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The number of matched strings is retrieved using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_match_info_get_match_count()"},{"type":"text","text":". To obtain the matched strings and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"their position you can use, respectively, ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_match_info_fetch()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_match_info_fetch_pos()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Note that the strings are returned in"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"reverse order of length; that is, the longest matching string is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"given first.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that the DFA algorithm is slower than the standard one and it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is not able to capture substrings, so backreferences do not work."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Setting "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"startPosition"},{"type":"text","text":" differs from just passing over a shortened"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"string and setting "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"notbol"},{"text":" in the case of a pattern","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that begins with any kind of lookbehind assertion, such as “\\b”.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unless "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"raw"},{"text":" is specified in the options, ","type":"text"},{"code":"string","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" must be valid UTF-8."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MatchInfo","isActive":true},{"text":" structure, used to get information on the match, is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"stored in ","type":"text"},{"code":"matchInfo","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if not ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Note that if "},{"code":"matchInfo","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"not ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" then it is created even if the function returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"i.e. you must free it regardless if regular expression actually","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"matched.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"string"},{"type":"text","text":" is not copied and is used in "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MatchInfo"},{"type":"text","text":" internally. If"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"you use any "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MatchInfo","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" method (except "},{"code":"g_match_info_free()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") after","type":"text"},{